00:13:28.259 --> 00:13:30.100
Again, it follows from Newton's
laws.

00:13:30.100 --> 00:13:31.470
You can calculate from Newton's
laws,

00:13:31.470 --> 00:13:35.538
because at every point,
wherever you may be,

00:13:35.538 --> 00:13:40.323
there's the force of gravity
acting this way and there is the

00:13:40.323 --> 00:13:44.629
perpendicular force from the
track acting this way,

00:13:44.629 --> 00:13:47.572
and the perpendicular force is
such that it cancels this part

00:13:47.572 --> 00:13:49.606
of gravity,
and this part of gravity will

00:13:49.606 --> 00:13:51.928
accelerate it and you can find
