00:27:29.130 --> 00:27:33.518
It's a fact--number 1,
here is a recipe for finding

00:27:33.518 --> 00:27:35.450
conservative forces.
 

00:27:35.450 --> 00:27:46.358
Take any function
U(x,y).

00:27:46.358 --> 00:27:47.858
I'm just going to do it in 2
dimensions.

00:27:47.858 --> 00:27:50.981
In 3 dimensions,
you can make it

00:27:50.981 --> 00:27:53.500
U(x,y,z).
 

00:27:53.500 --> 00:27:54.990
So let's give an example here.
 

00:27:54.990 --> 00:27:59.970
U = x^(3)y^(2).
 

00:27:59.970 --> 00:28:00.799
Take that function.
 

00:28:00.799 --> 00:28:01.848
You can write your own ticket.
 

00:28:01.848 --> 00:28:04.319
Write whatever function you
want, time hyperbolic

00:28:04.319 --> 00:28:06.122
sinh(y) times
cosh(x),

00:28:06.122 --> 00:28:07.099
