the property that

00:28:13.825 --> 00:28:18.740
F_x =
-dU/dx and

00:28:18.740 --> 00:28:23.868
F_y =
-dU/dy.

00:28:23.868 --> 00:28:25.656
In other words,
I'm going to manufacture a

00:28:25.656 --> 00:28:28.316
force whose x component
is - the x derivative of

00:28:28.316 --> 00:28:30.756
the function I picked and the
y component is - the

00:28:30.756 --> 00:28:32.980
y derivative of the
function I picked.

00:28:32.980 --> 00:28:35.923
So in my example,
F_x will be

00:28:35.923 --> 00:28:39.324
-x derivative partial
means keep y as a

00:28:39.324 --> 00:28:41.182
constant,
take the derivative with

00:28:41.182 --> 00:28:42.009
respect to x.
 

00:28:42.009 --> 00:28:48.960
That's 3x^(2)y and
F_y will be

00:28:48.960 --> 00:28:51.190
-2x^(3).
 

00:28:51.190 --> 00:28:58.588
3x^(2)y^(2) and
-2x^(3)y.

00:28:58.588 --> 00:29:02.785
Let me see if I got that right,
