00:29:16.349 --> 00:29:18.690
Why is this magic working?
 

00:29:18.690 --> 00:29:23.180
But let me write it in another
way that's more compact.

00:29:23.180 --> 00:29:26.048
So the force I want to get,
written as a vector,

00:29:26.048 --> 00:29:27.338
is i times
F_x,

00:29:27.338 --> 00:29:30.963
which is i times
−du/dx

00:29:30.963 --> 00:29:34.220
j times
−du/dy.

00:29:34.220 --> 00:29:36.910
That's the force I claim is
conservative.

00:29:36.910 --> 00:29:41.660
We're going to write that as -
grad U.

00:29:41.660 --> 00:29:45.365
This is called the grad and it
means gradient,

00:29:45.365 --> 00:29:48.660
and this symbol is shorthand
for this.

00:29:48.660 --> 00:29:53.220
There's nothing more to it.
 

00:29:53.220 --> 00:29:55.190
Gradient is a machine.
 

00:29:55.190 --> 00:29:56.348
Derivative is a machine.
 

00:29:56.348 --> 00:29:58.122
You give it a function,
sin x,

00:29:58.122 --> 00:30:00.190
it gives you an output,
