00:30:00.190 --> 00:30:02.519
you give it x squared,
it gives you 2x.

00:30:02.519 --> 00:30:04.700
Gradient is a different kind of
machine.

00:30:04.700 --> 00:30:06.714
You feed into it a function
U of x and

00:30:06.714 --> 00:30:08.866
y,
and it gives you a vector in

00:30:08.866 --> 00:30:11.980
all of the xy plane
obtained by taking the two

00:30:11.980 --> 00:30:14.046
derivatives,
one along x and one

00:30:14.046 --> 00:30:17.223
along y,
and assembling them into a

00:30:17.223 --> 00:30:18.640
single vector.
 

00:30:18.640 --> 00:30:21.910
So let's see for this
particular U,

00:30:21.910 --> 00:30:29.069
the force we have = -i
times 3x^(2)y^(2),

00:30:29.069 --> 00:30:34.098
